This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category as it deals with the development of an agent capable of playing text-based computer games through exploration and imitation learning. It also involves language understanding, problem-solving, and language generation by artificial agents, which are all topics related to artificial intelligence. 

The cs.CL sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with natural language processing in the context of text-based games. 

The cs.LG sub-category is another possibility as the paper involves the training of a policy to solve the game by imitating trajectories, which is a machine learning technique. 

The cs.GT sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with game theory in the context of text-based games. 

Finally, the cs.SE sub-category is a possibility as the paper involves the development of a software system for playing text-based games.
